---

### Erroneous Code Reference
```java
public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String variable;
        System.out.println(variable);
    }
}
```

### Debugging and Correction

**Error 1:** `String variable;` is not initialized.  
**Fix:** Initialize `variable` with a value.

**Error 2:** `System.out.println(variable);` will throw a `NullPointerException` because `variable` is not assigned a value.  
**Fix:** Initialize `variable` with a string.

---

### Corrected and Functional Code
```java
public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String variable = "Hello world";
        System.out.println(variable);
    }
}
```

All classes manage and manipulate the same original variable `variable` and perform the required operations.
